Happy Wednesday! Community Care is already off to a great start! We have a few reminders for families participating in Community Care: remember to complete the screener form before coming to school each day, and don't forget to bring your tech with you, students should bring their school issued device each day with their charger!

Bookmark the Self Screener linked here: http://bit.ly/HWselfscreen. Note, families are asked to wear face coverings and maintain 6 feet or more space in between other family groups outside of the building.

Classes are offered Mon - Fri from 2:30-3:30 weekly. All classes are free! Register here: www.artsandscraps.org/steam-in-a-bag-registration

During online learning, students were sharing how they missed being with each other in the midst of the covid pandemic.

Wanting to acknowledge and inspire, Ms. Rodgers decided to paint a butterfly in school colors representing transformation and hope. Due to the injustice that recently took place, students wanted to add a black butterfly to represent them—their resilience!

Although the painting is in draft form, Ms. Rodgers decided to leave it “unfinished” as a symbol of the work we all are presently doing and MUST continue to do. (The class will paint/color together this week.)

#wearedistinctive #dcpharperwoods #hope #resilience

Don’t forget we are still holding grab and go breakfast and lunch pick up at DCP-HW from 10-12p.

There are a number of providers working to ensure that you have ACCESS while school buildings are closed! We’re sharing a few resources that you may be interested in:

Comcast is: offering internet access during this time through free wifi hotspots, and making it easier to sign up for internet essentials. Comcast is providing unlimited data for cell customers, waiving late fees, and not disconnecting internet service if you reach out to let them know you cannot pay. Learn more at: https://corporate.comcast.com/covid-19

AT&T has temporarily suspended data caps, encouraging Americans to work from home and stream news sources without fear of data overage fees.

If you have additional resources, please share in the comments!

Tomorrow, Friday, March 13, our school will be closed. We are following the Detroit Public Schools decision to close. We apologize for the late notice, and any inconvenience this may cause, the safety of our students and staff is our top priority.

Staff will be on site Friday. We are preparing for the possible extended closure of school. DPS will share more information regarding the consideration of the extended closure of schools over the weekend. If schools will remain closed, we will have open office hours where families will have the opportunity to pick up packets or devices in preparation for remote learning (e-learning). More details to come!

Thank you for your patience, trust and support. Please reach out to your School Principal with any questions or concerns.

Good Morning DCPHW Families!

We can't wait to see you September 3rd for the first day of school!

Thank you to all our families who attended the Block Party, we had a great time celebrating with you!

Please note if you were unable to attend the DCP-Harper Woods Block Party this past Saturday we'd like you to stop by the main office THIS WEEK and drop off any missing documents, complete dismissal cards, transportation applications, and pick up your students class information.

The uniform store will also be open daily from 9a-4p.

Don't forget Gleaners on Friday 2-4p!

Thank you DCP Tigers! We are looking forward to an AMAZING year!
